<p><b>What is a chemical control?</b> In this context, the phrase "chemical control" refers to the use of specially formulated pesticides to kill or control plants.</p>
<p><b>What is PDC in engineering?</b> In civil engineering, PDC stands for "Preliminary Design Check." A Preliminary Design Check is a review of a design at an early stage in the design process, usually before the final design has been completed.</p>
<p><b>What is process control pdf?</b> Process control systems are used to automatically control the conditions of continuous production processes to ensure quality and efficiency. They combine control engineering and chemical engineering, using specialized control systems to regulate aspects like flow, output, and mixture based on sensor feedback.</p>
<p><b>What is the role of PDC in chemistry?</b> Pyridinium dichromate (PDC) is a strong oxidizing agent. It is able to convert primary alcohols to aldehydes, and secondary alcohols to ketones. Because of the associated toxicity of the reagent it is currently rarely used.</p>
<p><b>What is process control system in chemical industry?</b> Therefore, process control system continuously works to maintain the actual value of process parameter as much as close to the set point value. Moreover, in most of the plants, control of process parameters is very critical from safety and environment point of view.</p>
<p><b>What is the meaning of process control?</b> Process Control is the active changing of the process based on the results of process monitoring. Once the process monitoring tools have detected an out-of-control situation, the person responsible for the process makes a change to bring the process back into control.</p>
<p><b>What is SPC in chemical industry?</b> Statistical Process Control (SPC) is a necessary part of modern chemical processing. The software chosen to collect quality data and produce control charts will determine whether SPC is an awkward task or a smoothly operating part of the process.</p>
<p><b>What is a chemical processing system?</b> Chemical processing is done to change the chemical structure of raw (bulk) materials to obtain products of value to other industries / in daily life. These products include agrochemicals, petrochemicals, oleochemicals, ceramics, polymers, rubber, fragrances, flavors, and explosives.</p>